# Guidance for identity providers

This guidance is for identity providers connected to GOV.UK Verify. It will help you meet GOV.UK Verify standards when designing parts of the identity verification journey.

This guidance includes:

* GOV.UK Verify-specific [user research](/user-research) recommendations
* GOV.UK Verify-specific [design and content](/design-and-content) recommendations
* [accessibility and assisted digital](/accessibility) requirements for identity providers
* [design patterns](/design-patterns) based on findings from GDS research into identity verification
* [branding rules](/branding) for using the GOV.UK Verify brand and logos
* a template for the [3-monthly user research and interface report](/3-monthly-report)

You should also follow the guidance in the government [Service Manual](https://www.gov.uk/service-manual). It helps teams create and run digital services that meet the [Government Service Standard](https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/service-standard).

You also need to follow:

* the operations manual
* [identity proofing and authentication good practice guides](https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/identity-proofing-and-authentication)
* service delivery requirements

If you do not have access to these documents, please [contact the Verify team](mailto:idp_assurance@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk).
